{"word":"ἄγραφος","slug":"ἄγραφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄγραφος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γράφω'><el>γράφω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>unwritten</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>ἄγραφοι νόμοι</el> <i>unwritten laws</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>the laws of nature, moral law</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>laws of custom, common law</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>not registered</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b> <el>ἄγρει, ἀγρεῖτε</el>, <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <el>ἀγρέω.</el><p/></div>"}]}